Coloration in life. (Image 8 a-d in
Katwate et al. 2014 b
). Body yellow. Position of humeral and caudal spots same as described for preserved specimens, spot on caudal peduncle surrounded by a golden hoop covering scales 19–21 of lateral-line row, saddling caudal peduncle dorsally. Dorsal fin with 2–3 longitudinal rows of intense black spots, third one occupying only anterior portion of dorsal, yellow in breeding male, red and devoid of black spots in female. Pectoral, pelvic and anal fins yellow. Caudal fin yellow. Sclera bright yellow in breeding males, iridescent silver in females and immature males.
